            BUILDING AND INSTALLING GNU MPFR ON MS WINDOWS/64BIT
            ====================================================

Please also see the toplevel README.md for instructions.
These instructions are only for the impatient.  Others should read the toplevel
README.md for instructions.

[1] What do I need?

MS Visual C/C++ 2026 (possibly Community Edition - CE) installed on your
build host. Furthermore, a GNU patch(.exe) is required. You MAY install
GIT for Windows, which comes with a patch.exe.

[2] How do I build?

Enter the 'x64_x86 Native Tools Command Prompt' of MS Visual C/C++ or
'ARM64 Native Tools Command Prompt', respectively.
*DO NOT* use one of the 'Cross Tools Command Prompt' (e.g. ARM64 on x86-64)
unless you want to omit the execution of the test suite (the test suite
is only executable on the target platform!).

Download the original GNU MPFR sources, as of writing this text, it is
version 4.2.2. Untar it:

tar xfJ mpfr-4.2.2.tar.xz  # you may use any Linux-type environment, e.g.
                           # Window Linux subsystem, Cygwin, or Windows
                           # 7-ZIP to perform this.

Copy (recursively) the entire win64 folder of this contribution into the
newly created folder mpfr-4.2.2. Enter this folder via 'cd'.

--

The static library build is performed by:

nmake /f win64/Makefile  # builds static lib, tests, runs testsuite, builds
                         # tuneup.exe (NO ASSEMBLY)

nmake /f win64/Makefile ASSEMBLY=  # same but with assembly

The dynamic library (with static import library) build is performed by:

nmake /f win64/Makefile dynamic_lib check  # builds DLL and static import
                                           # library

nmake /f win64/Makefile ASSEMBLY= dynamic_lib check  # same with assembly

=> NEVER USE A BUILD **WITHOUT** HAVING EXECUTED THE TESTSUITE!!!

